@node "intro" "What got me thinking"


   Well, this program was not meant to be 'serious'. Since I got the
   december 1995 issue of CU Amiga my life was going to change enormously.
   
   On that very issue was a full version of Amiga E and a nice booklet also
   attached to the magazine. After some programming I discovered that
   programming the beloved AMIGA(tm) was not that easy...
   
   But after some fooling around I managed to get a simple protracker
   replayer up and running.(It only worked via the CLI, no fancy windows)
   But then my acquired knowledge of the OS did not seem to work out fine:
   The program crashed on practically everything else.
   
   But after 2 full years I can finally present the 'release' version of
   
   @{b}CLI-Tracker 1.0@{ub}
   
   
@endnode

@node "requirements" "What do I need to run this program?"

   All you need is:
   
   - An AMIGA(tm) Computer         - (Not included)
   
   - OS 2.04 or higher             - (Not included)
   
   - Some free CHIP memory         - (Not included)
   
   - Some standard Protracker mods - (Not included)
   
   - PTReplay.library              - Included
   
   - XFDMaster.library             - Included
   
   
   That's all folks...
   
@endnode
@node "features" "What's in it for me?"

  CLI-Tracker includes:
  
  - Nice CLI interface
  
  - Nice GUI Font sensitive and resizable
  
  - Nice Information window
  
  - XFDMaster support, for decrunching virtually every packed file
    (encrypted files are not supported at this moment...)
    
  - Small executable ~25KB
  
  - Can be made resident
  
  - Lots more... :)
  
 
@endnode
@node "usage" "How do I use this program?"

   Tough one...:)
   
   - Just type from your favourite shell:
   
     CLI-Tracker <name of da file>
   
     DO *NOT* INCLUDE QUOTATION MARKS IF FILE CONTAINS SPACES:
     CLI-TRACKER CAN HANDLE FILENAMES WITH SPACES AT THIS MOMENT...
   
     So type:
   
     CLI-Tracker mod.file with spaces in its name
   
     instead of:
   
     CLI-Tracker "mod.file with spaces in its name"
   
     IT WILL *NOT* WORK!!!
   
   
   - When running just click the close gadget to quit the program.
   
   
   
   Usage in Web Browsers...
   
   CLI-Tracker can be used to play Modules while you are online...
   
   Simply edit/make a MIME-type that defines a ProTracker module
   
   Then use CLI-Tracker as an external program
   
   Such as:
   
   CLI-Tracker %s
               ^^
               Should be replaced by whatever your browser uses to
               pass as an argument.
               
   
@endnode

